------------------------------------------------------------------------
r8234 | jdorje | 2006-06-20 22:17:06 +0200 (Di, 20 Jun 2006) | 1 line
Geänderte Pfade:
   M /trunk/ggz-client-libs/ggzcore/netxml.c

Don't send NULL language.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
r8230 | jdorje | 2006-06-20 17:18:04 +0200 (Di, 20 Jun 2006) | 8 lines
Geänderte Pfade:
   M /trunk/ggz-client-libs/ggzcore/netxml.c

- Drop CDATA chunks, as all we're sending is text and all we have to do
  is escape it to send it normally.
- Drop unescape() calls.

The way expat works is that we have to do the escaping but expat will
automatically unescape any incoming text.  Thus ggz_xml_unescape() should
never actually be used with expat.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r8183 | jdorje | 2006-06-13 01:15:12 +0200 (Di, 13 Jun 2006) | 1 line
Geänderte Pfade:
   M /trunk/ggz-client-libs/ggzcore/player.c

Don't crash when a player has no name.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
r8182 | jdorje | 2006-06-13 01:02:39 +0200 (Di, 13 Jun 2006) | 1 line
Geänderte Pfade:
   M /trunk/ggz-client-libs/ggzmod/ggzmod.h

Updated function documentation.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
r8119 | jdorje | 2006-06-07 09:23:30 +0200 (Mi, 07 Jun 2006) | 10 lines
Geänderte Pfade:
   M /trunk/ggz-client-libs/ggzmod/ggzmod.c
   M /trunk/ggz-client-libs/ggzmod/ggzmod.h

Add previously missing function ggzmod_is_ggz_mode.  This returns TRUE if
the program is being run in GGZ mode (as determined by environment variables).
With this function a program can determine if it should exit with an error or
if it should run in non-ggz mode.

One problem is that with embedded GGZ, once the embedded GGZ begins GGZ mode
is entered and is not left.  This is probably a bug elsewhere in ggzmod.  It's
not clear in this case whether the ggz mode environment variable should be
left unset, or if it should be cleared when embedded GGZ is complete.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r8116 | jdorje | 2006-06-07 04:34:17 +0200 (Mi, 07 Jun 2006) | 1 line
