   M /trunk/ggz-client-libs/m4/ggz.m4

- build system synchronisation


------------------------------------------------------------------------
r7377 | josef | 2005-08-13 12:27:52 +0200 (Sa, 13 Aug 2005) | 8 lines
Geänderte Pfade:
   M /trunk/ggz-client-libs/ggz-config/ggz-config.c

- new command line option --noregistry=/usr/share/games/modules/gtk-games

This should eliminate everyone's favourite ggz-config issue. When using
--noregistry, the modfile is not registered but preserved instead. Then,
during deinstallation, simply call:
for i in $dir/*.module.dsc; do ggz-config --remove --modfile $i; done


